programme.title: TechXplore
programme.desc: The BBC' s sport-loving tech presenter Paul Carter travels to Japan to dive into the Deaflympics, where elite performance meets cutting-edge innovation to smash barriers and supercharge inclusion. Across the deaf competitions, Paul tests universal translation tools that let athletes, staff and fans talk, sign and connect without missing a beat. He hits the athletics track to discover how vibrating starting blocks could shave off vital seconds, and he steps into a fan experience reimagined - from onomatopoeic scoreboards and live social feeds to devices that buzz, glow and thump in time with every moment. Even journeys between Tokyo venues reveal how new tech is helping deaf visitors navigate the city with greater ease. A celebration of tech-driven accessibility and a glimpse of a future where no fan, athlete or sporting moment is left out.

programme.title: Global Women
programme.desc: In Syria's new government, what difference can one woman make in a cabinet of men charged with moving a nation from war to peace? A little more than a year after Bashar Al-Assad's regime was ousted, ending decades of dictatorship, former opposition leader Hind Kabawat is tackling some of the toughest jobs in her Ministry of Social Affairs and Labour. 'I'm not here for window dressing!' is her rebuke to critics who say she's a token woman, a Christian, in the new order of President Ahmed al-Sharaa. The former commander linked to Al-Qaeda now positions himself as a pragmatist. His transitional government is still dominated by his close aides and some former fighters. For BBC Global Women, our Chief International Correspondent Lyse Doucet travelled to Syria to spend time with Hind Kabawat as she meets some of the millions of Syrians still living in dire poverty, displaced in tents or fearful of sectarian violence. She calls on the world to support Syria, and calls on her president to empower more women.

programme.title: Olivia Attwood: Getting Filthy Rich
programme.desc: Olivia first went to Vegas aged 21 and considers it to be her spiritual home. This time, armed with a ‘naughty list’, she’ll be tracking down the people turning pleasure into profit. Nevada is the only state in the US to allow licensed brothels and Olivia discovers how much money visitors will need at the legendary ‘Chicken Ranch’ to be shown a good time. A VIP limo service takes Olivia to one of the largest strip clubs in the world, where she learns from two veteran dancers that the big spenders are not always who you think they’d be. But it’s in Vegas’s unlicensed sex trade where the really big bucks can be made, with an estimated $5 billion dollars being spent on escorts each year. She meets a couple earning a fortune as high class escorts. Finally, Olivia meets fellow Brit Gal from Brighton, who is determined to make it big in the US porn industry. Gal invites Liv to her next porn shoot where she is co-starring with the legendary ‘Girthmaster.’

programme.title: Plebs
programme.desc: Sitcom following three desperate young men who reside in ancient Rome. Stylax buys Grumio an erotic vase for his birthday featuring a character who bears a striking resemblance to someone nearby, and Marcus - who is under pressure from the girls - suggests that they swap roles for the day. Meanwhile, Stylax hangs out with his cousin Lucretia, someone that he has an unusually close relationship with...

programme.desc: Shopping from home.

programme.title: Scooby-Doo! Mystery Incorporated
programme.desc: Animated mysteries. After an exchange student named Mai Lee shows up in town to stay with Velma, strange kung fu wizards begin attacking the town trying to get her - as it turns out, Mai Lee has a ring they are after. The gang decides to help, but friction arises when Shaggy develops a crush on Mai Lee that really gets under Velma's skin. Fortunately, they find an ally in Crystal Cove's tea shop owner Chen, who reveals to them that the wizards are after the Dragon's Heart, a mythical jewel that he just happens to be guarding. Now it is up to the gang to solve the mystery before they lose the Dragon's Heart - and Mai Lee - forever!

programme.title: Be Cool, Scooby-Doo!
programme.desc: Animated adventure series following Shaggy, Scooby, Velma, Daphne and Fred as they travel around on what could be their final summer break together. It's Christmas Eve and Fred is ready to solve a Christmas mystery - unfortunately, the gang has arrived in a town that's being attacked by a pterodactyl... and it doesn't seem to have anything to do with the festive season.

programme.title: Totally Bonkers Guinness World Records
programme.desc: Matt Edmondson narrates a funny selection of TV and home video clips featuring Guinness World Record attempts from around the world - this episode features the most teeth in a mouth, the fastest time to type a text message, the largest skinny dip, and the most coconuts smashed on a person's head with a baseball bat.

programme.title: Buying the View
programme.desc: House-hunting show that explores luxury listings in majestic mountain ranges, sprawling beaches, and glittering urban skylines. Armed with a budget of one-and-a-half million dollars, estate agent Greg McInnis help Kara-Lee and Anthony search the Haliburton Highlands for a lakefront getaway cottage that they want to become their forever home.

programme.title: The Only Way is Essex
programme.desc: Reality series. There's trouble in Essex as Dani spills the beans to Ella about Dan and Amber's phone call. Will hearing that he's still chatting to Amber throw Ella off? Later, Ella arrives late at Dani's birthday party and quizzes Dan about what the video call with Amber was about. Will his explanation reassure her and can they continue moving forward while he's still chatting to Amber? Amber gets upset about Dan and Chloe is worried she's losing her friendship with the boys. Elsewhere, The twins are turning one and everyone comes together to celebrate. Amy and Billy want a drama free day, but will they get their wish as Junaid approaches Chloe and Courtney to try and make up? Elma also has news for Amber about Ella and Dan. The birthday party isn't the place for an argument, but how will Amber handle the latest Della bombshell?

programme.title: The Only Way is Essex
programme.desc: Reality series. The whole Essex crew get together to celebrate Harry's 30th birthday. Meanwhile, Diags has come to some decisions about Jodie and talks to the lads about it. When they back him, he decides to bite the bullet and ask her to move in with him, but with so much else to consider, will she say yes? Saff has been avoiding Becks and Livvy for months - they were all at Jordan's party and at the 1920s fundraiser - but not a word was exchanged. Becks thinks it's time she finally confronts her. Will they be able to resolve their issues, or will it merely serve to fan the flames?

programme.title: Deal or No Deal
programme.desc: Paralympian Denise and her dog Sherpa aim to become 100,000-pound winners by opening the iconic red boxes, but the Banker stands in their way - join Stephen Mulhern to find out if the pair will take home a fortune or if the Banker will convince Denise to sell her box for a bargain.

programme.title: Deal or No Deal
programme.desc: Stephen Mulhern welcomes Brogan to the table as she hopes that her red box contains a 100,000-pound jackpot - the Banker, however, is hoping the opposite.

programme.title: Celebrity Catchphrase
programme.desc: Stephen Mulhern hosts a celebrity special of the classic game show with Nikki Fox, Robert Rinder, and Georgia Taylor all trying to 'say what they see' as they guess well-known phrases for the chance to win a 50,000-pound jackpot for their chosen charity.

programme.title: The Masked Singer
programme.desc: Joel Dommett is joined by panellists Maya Jama, Jonathan Ross, Davina McCall, Mo Gilligan and special guest Samantha Barks for the seventh series Grand Final as TV's biggest musical mystery - the top-secret singing show where a superstar line-up disguised in head-to-toe costumes and compete to remain anonymous - is finally solved. As each celebrity sings, the superstar panel and the studio audience are left asking 'Who is behind the mask?' - in this episode, the final three Masked Singers compete to be crowned champion, the identities of all three finalists will finally be revealed, and previous Masked Singers Lionfish, Pufferfish and Snail all return for three one-of-a-kind duets.

Now elected to Congress, Evan has recently moved with his wife and children to Virginia so that he can begin his political career. However, when Evan is about to take the Pledge of Allegiance for the first time, God visits him. His life is then turned upside down when God asks him to build an Ark ahead of a great flood. Although Evan pledged to change the world in the slogan for his run for Congress, Evan is nevertheless sceptical of God's order. However, a series of unusual events - including flocks of birds swarming upon Evan - eventually change his mind. How will Evan fulfil God's will, build an Ark, and survive the flood?
